data.meta_description:
Images documenting the Radiological Survey of Eniwetok, Bikini and Rongelap Atolls between July and September 1964.

Caption with image: The Ran-Annim is shown lying at anchor off Bikini Island, framed by fronds of a coconut palm growing on the beach.  Sleeping quarters for the scientists were closely packed double-decker bunks covered with canvas at the after end of the upper deck.  The No.2 cargo hold was rigged up as a laboratory area. 9267-22A

Radiological Survey of Bikini, Eniwetok and Rongelap Atolls, Volume 2, p.43.
